title: Index of Payrolls, Furniture for United States
notes:
Series Is Presented Here As Two Variables-- (1)--Original Data, 1919-1942 (2)--Original Data, 1947-1954. This Series Ends On The 1923-1925=100 Base, But The New Revised Series Starts In 1939 On A 1939 Base. Source: For 1919-1930, Bureau Of Labor Statistics, Bulletin No. 610, "Revise Indexes Of Factory Employment And Payrolls: 1919-1933, " (1935); For 1931-1934, Bureau Of Labor Statistics, Mimeographed Tables Of September, 1938; For 1935-1939: Bureau Of Labor Statistics, Mimeographed Tables Of May, 1940; For 1940-1942, "Employment And Payrolls" And Monthly Labor Review.

This NBER data series m08133a appears on the NBER website in Chapter 8 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter08.html.
